  "prompt": "What is the best gaming PC I can get for 1400\u20ac?",
  "response": "Selecting the best gaming PC within your budget of 1400\u20ac depends on various factors including the types of games you play, the resolution and settings you prefer, and whether you are open to building your own PC or prefer a pre-built system. As of late 2023, here are some considerations and recommendations for components that can fit a 1400\u20ac budget:\n\n### Building Your Own PC:\nBuilding your own PC often provides the best value and customization options. Here is a sample build for around 1400\u20ac:\n\n#### CPU:\n- AMD Ryzen 5 5600X or Intel Core i5-12600K: Both are excellent choices for gaming, providing strong single-core performance and efficient multi-core capabilities.\n\n#### GPU:\n- NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti or AMD Radeon RX 6700 XT: These GPUs offer excellent performance at 1080p and 1440p resolutions and are well-suited for most modern games.\n\n#### Motherboard:\n- MSI B550 Tomahawk or ASRock B550 Pro4 (for AMD)\n- ASUS TUF Gaming Z690-Plus WiFi D4 or MSI PRO Z690-A WIFI (for Intel)\n\n#### RAM:\n- 16GB (2 x 8GB) DDR4-3600 CL16: Brands like Corsair, G.Skill, and Kingston are reputable.\n\n#### Storage:\n- 1TB NVMe SSD: Samsung 970 EVO Plus, WD Black SN750, or Crucial P5 offer fast speeds and ample storage for games and applications.\n\n#### Power Supply:\n- 650W or 750W 80+ Gold Certified PSU: Seasonic, Corsair, and EVGA are reliable suppliers.\n\n#### Case:\n- Mid-tower case with good airflow: NZXT H510, Fractal Design Meshify C, or Phanteks P300A.\n\n#### Cooling:\n- Stock cooler for the CPU should be sufficient, but consider an aftermarket cooler like the Cooler Master Hyper 212 or Noctua NH-U12S for better cooling and quieter performance.\n\n### Pre-Built Systems:\nIf you prefer a pre-built system, many manufacturers offer gaming PCs within your budget that should meet your requirements:\n\n#### ASUS ROG, Alienware, and HP Omen:\nBrands like ASUS ROG, Alienware, and HP Omen offer pre-built gaming desktops designed for performance and ease of use.\n\n#### Example Models:\n- **ASUS ROG Strix G15**: Comes with a Ryzen 5 5600X and RTX 3060 Ti, often found within your budget range.\n- **HP Omen 30L**: Often features Intel i5 CPUs and RTX 3060 or RTX 3060 Ti, providing solid gaming performance.\n- **Dell G5 Gaming Desktop**: Usually offers competitive components including Intel i5 or Ryzen CPUs paired with RTX 3060 GPUs.\n\n### Tips for Maximizing Value:\n- **Sales and Discounts**: Keep an eye out for seasonal sales, Black Friday deals, and other promotions.\n- **Local Retailers and Online Stores**: Compare prices between local retailers and online stores like Amazon, Newegg, and Micro Center.\n\n### Final Considerations:\nEnsure that the case has sufficient cooling and space for future upgrades. Also, consider the ease of installation and compatibility of components if you are building your own PC.\n\nBy choosing a combination of the above components or opting for a reputable pre-built system, you can get an excellent gaming PC within your 1400\u20ac budget that will provide smooth and enjoyable gaming experiences.",
